comment0.text=\r\n\ \ A\ super\ light\ calculator.\r\n\ \r\n\ <p>\ It\ uses\ MVC\ (Model-View-Controller)\ structure.\ And\ a\ {@link\ Main}\ class,\ which\ runs\ as\ a\ javafx\ application.\r\n\ View\ includes\ four\ action\ buttons,\ but\ only\ the\ add(+)\ button\ works.\r\n\ \r\n\ <p>\ There\ is\ also\ a\ simple\ {@link\ Calculator}\ class,\ which\ does\ the\ calculation\ add(+),\ sub(-),\ mul(\u00D7),div(/).\r\n\ It\ also\ contains\ unit\ test\ class\ {@link\ CalculatorTest}\ which\ test\ Calculator,\r\n\ you\ need\ to\ write\ your\ testing\ code\ if\ you\ want\ to\ do\ Junit\ testing.\ \r\n\ \r\n\ <p>\ It\ also\ include\ a\ .css\ file\ to\ stylize\ the\ interface.\r\n\ \r\n\ <h2>Project\ features</h2>\r\n\ <p>Your\ code\ includes\ the\ following\ features\ which\ will\ all\ gain\ marks\ if\ you\ use\ them\ in\ \r\n\ your\ project\ code\:\r\n\ \r\n\ <ul>\r\n\ <li>control\ statements\ (loops,\ if\ etc)</li>\ done\r\n\ <li>using\ classes,\ objects\ and\ methods</li>\ done\r\n\ <li>inheritance</li>\r\n\ <li>encapsulation\ and\ protected\ variables</li>\ done\r\n\ <li>using\ collection\ classes\ (TreeMap)</li>\r\n\ <li>JUnit\ tests</li>\ can\ defo\ do\r\n\ <li>Javadoc\ comments\ and\ compiled\ documentation</li>\ can\ defo\ do\r\n\ <li>code\ comments</li>\ done\r\n\ <li>using\ file\ IO\ for\ persistent\ storage</li>\ done\r\n\ </ul>\r\n\ \r\n\ \r\n\ @author\ Shine\r\n\ @version\ 2025-CI401-Calcualtor\r\n
